Wisconsin LAB Election Investigation Summary: Dirty Voter Rolls Lead to Dirty Elections  

The Wisconsin Legislative Audit Bureau (LAB) was authorized by the Joint Legislative Audit Committee on February 11, 2021 to audit the 2020 election. The LAB review is one of several ongoing election integrity efforts in WI: Special Counsel Mike Gableman is pursing an investigation under the supervision of Speaker Robin Vos and Reps. Janel Brandtjen and Timothy Ramthum continue to fight for a full forensic audit of ballots and machines. 

LAB released its report on Friday, after receiving limited cooperation from election officials:

 • Only 2 of 6 Wisconsin Election Commissioners agreed to interview with the auditors;

• The City of Madison (2nd most populous in Wisconsin) and Milwaukee County (most populous) did not allow LAB to physically handle election records, including ballots and absentee ballot certificates, citing chain of custody concerns;

 • More than half (52%) of state municipal clerks and 18% of county clerks did not respond to the auditors request for information. 

Despite these barriers, the audit team made several disturbing discoveries. Overall, the findings reinforce Patrick Colbeck’s determination that election fraud originates with the Qualified Voter File. Dirty voter rolls lead to dirty elections. 

WEC Ignored National Database That Identifies Potential Problems

Among the most alarming revelations in the LAB investigation is the fact that the Wisconsin Election Commission (WEC) did not use the ERIC (Electronic Registration Information Center) database to check for fraudulent voters. ERIC allows states to determine if residents are voting in multiple states, have died in other states, moved within the state, voted multiple times in the same election, or are eligible to vote but not registered.

It turns out the first time WEC ran an ERIC report on registered voters was in May 2021, after the auditors started poking around. The only ERIC report it ran in 2020 was for eligible voters who weren’t registered.

New Voter Registration Non-Matches

In 2020, nearly 1M people registered to vote in WI. This is a shockingly high number given that just under 3.3M people voted in the 2020 WI election and there are only 3.68M registered voters in WI.  

LAB found that 45,665 of these newly registered voters signed up with state IDs or driver’s licenses that did not match DMV records, a potential indication of fraud. The WEC did not even attempt to match IDs on another 13,800 registrations. In total, nearly 60K newly registered voters had no ID verification, which is a violation of the Help America Vote Act (HAVA), which requires voters to provide a driver’s license (or social security information) when they register.

Good Evening County GOP Leaders, Affiliated Organizations and Ad-hoc Committee Members:


Today's Full Forensic Physical and Cyber Audit Update (FFPCA) will focus on the Legislative Audit Bureau's Report (LAB) on Election Administration of the November 3, 2020 Federal Election.


Many members of the Ad-hoc Committee, individuals, County GOP Leaders and Affiliated Organizations have weighed in on their take of the LAB Election Administration Report from Friday, October 22nd. The LAB was never asked to conduct a full forensic physical and cyber audit (FFPCA). They were simply asked in February of 2021 to conduct a "review" of "elections administration" of the November 3, 2020 Federal Election in Wisconsin (see attached LAB 1 and LAB 2). LAB's hands appear to have been tied from the onset of their "review" of "elections administration" by Senator Cowles (R) and Representative Kerkman (R) of the Joint Legislative Audit Committee.


Here are some of the take aways from the LAB Election Administration Report:


There was no full forensic physical and cyber audit (FFPCA) conducted in spite of what the media and press are trying to report non-stop. Voting machines were not examined for possibly being compromised as alleged by democrats since 2016, ballots were not kinematically processed for what is believed to be thousands of possible fake ballots and there were no canvassing efforts of the thousands of suspicious addresses of supposed actual voters.

Very limited cooperation from some election officials. The Brandtjen Subpoenas would have forced this without granting immunity to any individuals unlike what the Vos/Gableman Subpoenas appear to be doing while being argued in Court as predicted by the Wisconsin Ad-hoc Committee for the FFPCA.

2 of the 6 Wisconsin Election Commission Members (WEC) were interviewed. One WEC Member submitted a written response and the other 3 declined to be interviewed.

The City of Madison refused to permit the LAB to physically handle any election-related materials. Can anyone say, "Voting in the Park?"

Only 48% of the statewide Municipal Clerks (1,500 +/-) responded to the LAB while 82% of the 72 County Clerks responded to the LAB.

WEC has largely ignored using the Electronic Registration Information Center (ERIC) for years that would have easily identified voters voting in multiple states, have died in other states, moved within a state, voted multiple times in the same election and or are eligible to vote but not registered.

45,665 new voters registered in 2020 without matching information (their name) from the Department of Motor Vehicles (DMV) that WEC appears to not be concerned about.

WEC appears to not attempt to match 13,800 new voter records.

The difference for the Presidential Candidates in the November 3, 2020 in Wisconsin was allegedly 20,540 votes.

New online registrants signatures were not checked with the signatures on-file with the Department of Transportation (DOT) by WEC.

The LAB reviewed (by eye) 14,710 of the 1.96 million absentee ballots cast statewide. Some of the absentee ballot issues discovered by the LAB include, but aren't limited to, only a partial witness address, no witness address, no witness signature and or no voter signature, but were still apparently recorded as a vote, which is in direct violation of Wisconsin State Statute 6.48 (2) and 5.01 (1).

Felons (8), deceased absentee votes (11) and dual voter accounts (24) were discovered by the LAB.

33,473 deceased individuals matched records in the state voter system were identified for 2020 without WEC apparently being concerned or acting on it.

169,901 individuals declared themselves indefinitely confined for the first time in 2020. 48,554 indefinitely confined voters do not have a photo id on file where they are registered to vote.

1,001 individuals who declared themselves indefinitely confined voted in-person at the polls on November 3, 2020.

FDA-Experte: "Wir erfahren nie, wie sicher der Impfstoff ist – bis wir ihn verabreichen" https://de.rt.com/nordamerika/126265-fda-gremiumsmitglied-wir-erfahren-nie/

Ein stimmberechtigtes Mitglied eines beratenden Ausschusses der US-amerikanischen Arzneimittelbehörde (Food and Drug Administration; FDA) räumte am Dienstag ein, dass die Frage, ob der COVID-19-Impfstoff von Pfizer für 5- bis 11-jährige Kinder sicher ist oder nicht, erst dann vollständig geklärt werden könne, wenn er verabreicht wird. Das Ausschussmitglied Dr. Eric Rubin sagte während der Anhörung:

"Wir werden nie erfahren, wie sicher der Impfstoff ist, bis wir anfangen, ihn zu verabreichen. So ist es nun einmal."

Trotz des Eingeständnisses von Dr. Rubin fiel die Entscheidung des Gremiums am Ende bis auf eine Enthaltung einstimmig zugunsten der formellen Empfehlung des COVID-19-Impfstoffs von Pfizer für Kinder im Rahmen der derzeitigen Notfallzulassung aus. Die vollständige Zulassung durch die FDA wird in den nächsten Tagen erwartet, gefolgt von der Prüfung durch die US-amerikanischen Zentren für Krankheitskontrolle (CDC) in der nächsten Woche.
